pageContext.claim: “The very rude elevator screamers are paid professionals only looking to make Senators look bad. Don’t fall for it! Also, look at all of the professionally made identical signs. Paid for by Soros and others. These are not signs made in the basement from love! #Troublemakers”
pageContext.analysis: Some protesters were given stipends to assist with possible bail payments. There's no evidence liberal billionaire George Soros paid people to protest Brett Kavanaugh's nomination to the Supreme Court. Soros's Open Society Foundations gave grants for other, specific programs to one of the groups protesting Kavanaugh. That grant money came with strings attached -- most of it was designated for Puerto Rico rebuilding after Hurricane Maria -- and was not used to pay protesters.
